{{Quote|May the Force be with you. I am Kun, Jedi archaeologist.|Exar Kun to [[Cay Qel-Droma]] and [[Tott Doneeta]]|<ref name="Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 2">[[Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 2|''Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith'' 2]]</ref>}}
A '''Jedi archaeologist''' was a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] who had achieved the rank of [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Knight]] and had chosen to specialize in the practices of the [[Jedi Consular|Consular]], specifically the field of [[Archaeology/Legends|archaeology]].

==Overview==
Under the umbrella title of [[Jedi Researcher|''Researcher'']], archaeologists often attended the [[Academy of Jedi Archaeology]] to perfect their skills. The academy in turn, was an affiliate of the [[Jedi Service Corps/Legends|Jedi Service Corps]]' [[Exploration Corps/Legends|Exploration Corps]] branch. Traveling out into [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] and uncover ancient artifacts, the archaeologists would turn over all findings to the [[Educational Corps]] for deciphering and translation.<ref name="TJP" />

As a specialized field, there weren't a large number of archaeologists active at one time. During the [[Great Sith War/Legends|Great Sith War]], the Jedi [[Exar Kun/Legends|Exar Kun]], who was in the process of being seduced to the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]], told Master [[Arca Jeth]] when he arrived on [[Onderon/Legends|Onderon]], that he was connected with the academy. Kun asked for access to the tomb of [[King/Legends|King]] [[Ommin/Legends|Ommin]], a dark side practitioner. Having no reason to deny the young Jedi, Jeth unknowingly helped Kun gain access to dark side artifacts that would further his progress down the path to the dark side.<ref name="Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith">''[[Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith]]''</ref>

Several millennia later, the [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Jocasta Nu/Legends|Jocasta Nu]] would work with the ExplorCorps as an archaeologist, discovering much on her journey that would eventually lead to her appointment as [[Jedi archivist/Legends|Chief Librarian]] of the [[Jedi Archives/Legends|Jedi Archives]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. During her adventures, Nu discovered the [[Miraluka/Legends|Miraluka]] [[Jerec (Inquisitor)|Jerec]], who she would eventually take on as a [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]], instilling in him the same love for archaeology.<ref name="DB-Nu, Jocasta">{{DB|character|jocastanu|Nu, Jocasta}}</ref>

